38:29.742 --> 38:30.960
No, it's not.

38:31.961 --> 38:34.486
And I guess you're right,
we... um...

38:35.313 --> 38:36.792
I think as you get older,

38:38.533 --> 38:42.929
you, um, find yourself
needing someone

38:42.972 --> 38:45.801
to hold accountable for life

38:46.454 --> 38:49.675
not turning out exactly
as you'd imagined it.

38:51.111 --> 38:52.504
Jesus, dad.

38:52.939 --> 38:53.983
I know.

38:55.768 --> 38:59.641
But listen to me, not every
relationship has to be that.

39:01.513 --> 39:03.471
I mean, having said that,
most are.

39:05.430 --> 39:06.735
Okay.

39:07.606 --> 39:11.479
On that happy note.
How's it going with Taylor?

39:12.611 --> 39:14.003
It's going really well.

39:17.572 --> 39:20.619
Yeah? Good, that's good.

39:20.662 --> 39:21.837
That's very good.

39:24.449 --> 39:25.667
Are you in love?

39:32.021 --> 39:34.023
Yeah. I am.

39:35.721 --> 39:37.853
Wow. No shit.

39:41.466 --> 39:43.729
Yeah, well, I'm happy for you,
sweetheart.

39:44.512 --> 39:46.993
I'm so happy.
I'm so happy for you.

39:48.821 --> 39:49.822
Thanks.

39:55.697 --> 39:57.743
You make sure
she understands your worth.

39:59.397 --> 40:02.008
- I know. She does.
-She better.

40:03.313 --> 40:04.489
She damn well better.

40:15.543 --> 40:16.979
Your daughter is in love.

40:18.981 --> 40:20.461
Did you tell her to be careful?

40:20.766 --> 40:21.767
No.

40:24.552 --> 40:26.119
Told her to enjoy herself.

40:29.862 --> 40:32.734
To realize one's destiny
is a person's only obligation.

40:32.778 --> 40:34.910
Uh, and so, uh, he begins
listening to the desert,

40:34.954 --> 40:37.391
and, uh discovering
the soul of the world,

40:37.652 --> 40:39.480
which then inevitably,
uh, leads us to--

40:39.524 --> 40:40.742
All right, stop.

40:41.743 --> 40:42.918
You get a B.

40:43.223 --> 40:45.268
-But I'm not finished.
-Take a seat.

40:48.228 --> 40:49.534
I thought it was great.

40:49.577 --> 40:50.752
Let me ask you a question.

40:52.145 --> 40:53.755
Are you guys getting anything
out of this shit?

40:54.103 --> 40:55.322
Yeah.

40:55.365 --> 40:58.107
Good. Because I have to say,
I am as well.

40:58.412 --> 41:01.981
I mean, you're all rather
a solid group of young adults,

41:02.024 --> 41:03.504
and I enjoy your company.

41:03.548 --> 41:07.247
Yeah. Yeah, uh, I'd say
we're all pretty mature.

41:08.030 --> 41:11.773
Well, maturity is really just
another word for...

41:12.295 --> 41:13.383
how much misery you'd swallow.

41:13.819 --> 41:15.037
Yeah, totally.

41:16.691 --> 41:17.431
I'm talking about the
piss and shit of others, Rose,

41:17.475 --> 41:18.650
not your own.

41:19.128 --> 41:20.739
Do you mind if I smoke a joint?

41:20.782 --> 41:22.218
Mm-mm.

41:22.828 --> 41:23.785
Um...

41:24.612 --> 41:25.613
Thanks.

41:27.049 --> 41:28.834
I'm more than happy to help,
uh, pick up his classes,

41:28.877 --> 41:30.792
if that helps at all.

41:33.316 --> 41:34.927
You got to be
kidding me.

41:35.623 --> 41:38.017
Is he smoking
a marijuana cigarette?

41:38.060 --> 41:41.542
Uh, look, um,
maybe he's just trying to be--

41:41.586 --> 41:43.283
Fucking unbelievable.

41:44.066 --> 41:45.546
Oh, Richard.

41:49.724 --> 41:51.421
Why are you wearing sunglasses?

41:53.032 --> 41:55.600
I have cancer,
I'm supposed to wear sunglasses

41:55.643 --> 41:57.297
in unusual places.

41:57.340 --> 41:58.341
Yeah.

42:02.607 --> 42:05.174
Excuse me,
can we have two more please?

42:06.611 --> 42:08.874
Uh, no, uh, the check please.

42:11.006 --> 42:12.181
Why?

42:12.225 --> 42:15.837
Look, you're coming with me.

42:15.881 --> 42:17.360
I don't wanna go with you.

42:18.492 --> 42:19.928
Peter,
where are we going?

42:19.972 --> 42:21.669
I'm taking you
to support group.

42:21.713 --> 42:23.497
A support group
for what?

42:23.541 --> 42:24.672
-Cancer.
-Oh, Jesus.

42:26.152 --> 42:27.370
Want me to help you
with your sabbatical,

42:27.414 --> 42:28.763
then do this for me.
This is not easy for me,

42:28.807 --> 42:30.199
it's actually, it's quite hard.

42:30.243 --> 42:33.420
Uh, I understand that, but,
you know, it's my death.

42:33.725 --> 42:34.856
Yeah.

42:35.944 --> 42:37.119
What the fuck is this?

42:37.163 --> 42:38.991
Well, it's, uh, it's Barbara's.

42:39.295 --> 42:41.776
Eww. Um, I'm not getting in.

42:41.820 --> 42:44.126
Shut up,
and get in the damn car.

42:45.650 --> 42:46.999
It actually drives quite nice.

42:47.695 --> 42:48.696
Door.

42:49.654 --> 42:51.220
- Here you go.
-Well done.

42:55.790 --> 43:00.403
After 20 years of marriage,
I thought she'd, you know,

43:00.882 --> 43:03.058
stick around until I died.

43:04.538 --> 43:06.932
At least, I hoped she would.

43:08.455 --> 43:11.197
But, I guess,
it was really no point,

43:11.545 --> 43:14.592
you know, I guess it makes
more sense for her

43:14.635 --> 43:16.245
to move on now.

43:19.031 --> 43:21.424
But despite all that, I'm-I'm...

43:22.425 --> 43:23.949
I'm feeling pretty good.

43:24.253 --> 43:26.821
I'm doing okay.

43:27.082 --> 43:28.083
Uh-hmm.

43:28.823 --> 43:29.824
Thank you.

43:31.304 --> 43:33.393
Thank you for sharing
the journey of your battle, Ed.

43:33.436 --> 43:34.699
Uh-hmm.

43:35.264 --> 43:37.484
All right.
Whenever you're ready.

43:40.269 --> 43:43.229
Uh, my name is Peter,
I'm healthy,

43:44.143 --> 43:45.623
I don't have cancer,

43:47.102 --> 43:48.800
at least I don't think I do.

43:48.843 --> 43:49.888
Um...

43:51.019 --> 43:52.194
my friend,

43:53.152 --> 43:54.501
Richard does.

43:54.544 --> 43:57.243
And I thought that he could here
and talk about it.

44:00.638 --> 44:01.639
I'm...

44:03.336 --> 44:04.293
scared,

44:05.643 --> 44:06.774
I'm worried,

44:08.123 --> 44:11.300
I don't wanna lose
my best friend.

44:11.561 --> 44:12.737
Oh.

44:12.780 --> 44:14.869
That is really very lovely
of you, Peter.

44:15.391 --> 44:18.307
Thank you for sharing
the journey of your...

44:20.135 --> 44:21.310
battle.

44:22.485 --> 44:23.835
All right, Richard.

44:23.878 --> 44:25.924
-Whenever you're ready.

44:26.576 --> 44:29.405
Oh, no, no, no.
I'm not doing this. No, no.

44:30.232 --> 44:31.973
-Come on.
-I have nothing to say.

44:32.321 --> 44:34.106
- It's good for you.
-Uh, well, um,

44:34.149 --> 44:35.716
why don't you start
with your diagnosis?

44:35.760 --> 44:38.676
-Uh-hmm.
- Uh, I'd rather not,

44:38.980 --> 44:41.287
I'd actually prefer
to leave this place

44:41.330 --> 44:43.115
because the lighting
is poor down here,

44:43.158 --> 44:45.552
and it smells like urinal cakes
and sugar cookies.

44:45.595 --> 44:47.075
Uh, well, you find that if you--

44:47.119 --> 44:48.511
if you start
with your diagnosis--

44:48.555 --> 44:50.426
I think that you're gonna find
that I already know

44:50.470 --> 44:53.125
that I disagree with whatever
you're about to say.

44:53.516 --> 44:56.171
Peter, let's go.
We'll give it another shot.

44:57.433 --> 45:01.176
Would anyone else like to go
and grab a drink,

45:01.220 --> 45:03.701
and escape
this emotional circle jerk?

45:04.876 --> 45:06.094
What about you?

45:06.138 --> 45:07.705
You might need a drink or two.

45:09.707 --> 45:11.491
Richard, I--I've got cancer.

45:11.926 --> 45:13.188
So do I.

45:13.623 --> 45:16.539
Well, best of luck
with your impending deaths.

45:16.583 --> 45:18.759
-Yeah, you, too.
-Thank you.

45:20.152 --> 45:23.372
Oh, Richard, you gotta stay.
Uh, I wanna help you.

45:23.416 --> 45:24.939
Peter, no.

45:25.940 --> 45:27.768
I'd die here, and my corpse

45:27.812 --> 45:30.510
is nothing more than
a breeding ground for ticks.

45:31.729 --> 45:33.121
Plus, this way,

45:33.600 --> 45:35.994
I get to collect my salary
until the bitter end.

45:36.037 --> 45:37.299
Uh-huh.

45:38.039 --> 45:39.998
Maybe even after,
depending on

45:40.041 --> 45:44.219
how quickly it takes me
to find, my, uh, body.

45:46.004 --> 45:47.005
Oh.

45:52.880 --> 45:55.361
I have to leave for, uh...

45:56.623 --> 45:58.016
for Olivia's sake.

45:58.059 --> 45:59.104
No.

45:59.147 --> 46:01.106
Oh, no, no, come on. Listen.

46:01.149 --> 46:03.499
-Uh, yeah.
-All right. I'm gonna...

46:03.848 --> 46:06.067
-I am so sorry.
-I know.

46:12.247 --> 46:13.422
My friend.

46:15.903 --> 46:18.123
Oh, Richard.

46:19.167 --> 46:21.039
-Listen to me.
-Yeah.

46:21.082 --> 46:23.693
I think it's time to go
up to Canada.

46:23.737 --> 46:25.478
-No. I don't--
-Yeah.

46:28.916 --> 46:31.527
Peter, you know
they're talking about us.

46:35.444 --> 46:38.273
Hi. Hello, Professor Brown.

46:38.796 --> 46:40.841
-Hey, Claire.
-What are you doing here?

46:40.885 --> 46:42.582
-Nice to see you.
-Nice to see you.

46:42.625 --> 46:43.888
This is-- Claire, uh...

46:43.931 --> 46:45.237
This is Claire
and this is Peter.

46:45.280 --> 46:46.412
- Hi.
-Nice to see you.

46:46.455 --> 46:49.197
She's, in fact,
a niece of Henry Wright.

46:49.241 --> 46:51.156
Henry, Henry? Oh, how wonderful.

46:51.199 --> 46:52.897
That's great, good to meet you.

46:52.940 --> 46:55.421
You don't have to say that shit
because she despises him

46:55.464 --> 46:57.727
-as much as we do.
-Don't say things like that.

46:58.250 --> 47:00.078
He's all right, Henry Wright.

47:00.121 --> 47:02.558
He's perfectly right.

47:03.255 --> 47:04.865
I'll have another three please.

47:04.909 --> 47:07.041
-No, I don't want go.
-No, no, you're--

47:07.085 --> 47:09.174
-I'm having fun.
-You're behaving like a troll.

47:09.217 --> 47:10.436
We gotta go.

47:12.612 --> 47:14.614
Has anyone ever told you
that you're beautiful?

47:15.006 --> 47:16.137
Thank you, Peter.

47:16.659 --> 47:17.704
Good boy.

47:19.097 --> 47:21.795
Okay. That's it. Okay.
Get in the car. Just get--

47:21.839 --> 47:22.840
Ow.

47:23.188 --> 47:25.103
Hey, can I, uh,
buy you a nightcap?

47:25.843 --> 47:26.931
Nightcap?

47:27.322 --> 47:29.585
Hmm.
Barbara's gonna kill me.

47:30.021 --> 47:31.936
Would you be
disappointed if I said no?

47:31.979 --> 47:33.154
Was it a Mini Cooper?

47:33.198 --> 47:34.329
Yes.

47:35.330 --> 47:37.158
-Goodnight, Peter.
-Night.

47:37.202 --> 47:38.812
-Richard?
- Yeah.

47:39.030 --> 47:40.031
Love you.

47:41.467 --> 47:43.948
I'd like to say
how much I admire your bravery.

47:45.036 --> 47:46.602
Bravery for what?

47:49.605 --> 47:51.216
For being who you are,

47:53.000 --> 47:54.872
and doing so, unflinchingly.

47:55.263 --> 47:57.875
That's not bravery,
that's apathy.

48:00.834 --> 48:02.053
No, it's not.

48:06.884 --> 48:08.537
I'm gonna go put on some music.

48:47.228 --> 48:48.316
♪ I...

48:48.360 --> 48:50.362
Are you all right?

48:50.405 --> 48:52.494
♪ ...never had no one

48:52.538 --> 48:53.931
Um...

48:55.410 --> 48:56.585
no.

48:58.587 --> 48:59.937
No, I'm not.

49:05.638 --> 49:06.944
I got cancer.

49:09.163 --> 49:11.470
It's all right.
Everyone my age has cancer.

49:13.907 --> 49:16.214
For some reason, it just
never really kind of...

49:17.171 --> 49:18.520
hit until...

49:20.261 --> 49:22.960
now, what it really means.

49:25.571 --> 49:27.790
You know, because I'm gonna die.

49:32.317 --> 49:34.754
I mean, I'm really gonna die.

49:38.627 --> 49:40.760
-I'm sorry, Richard.
- Oh.

49:43.284 --> 49:46.287
Do me a favor, please keep
that between us, yeah?

49:46.635 --> 49:47.680
Okay.

49:48.333 --> 49:50.074
You're the only person
I've ever told,

49:50.117 --> 49:51.597
outside of Peter.

49:51.901 --> 49:53.860
♪ And I

49:54.643 --> 49:56.558
♪ Never had no one...

49:56.602 --> 49:58.647
Haven't even told
my wife and daughter yet.

50:04.566 --> 50:06.046
Come dance with me.

50:07.569 --> 50:08.570
Dance?

50:11.225 --> 50:12.444
I don't dance.

50:14.141 --> 50:15.403
Dance tonight.

50:16.491 --> 50:17.492
Okay.

50:23.324 --> 50:26.762
♪ And I

50:26.806 --> 50:29.635
♪ Never have no one

50:30.723 --> 50:33.378
♪ In times of trouble

50:34.640 --> 50:36.555
♪ I stood alone

50:37.947 --> 50:39.384
What do I do now?

50:39.427 --> 50:42.474
♪ And now

50:42.822 --> 50:45.825
♪ I'm so much stronger...

50:45.868 --> 50:47.000
Is this it?

50:47.435 --> 50:48.480
Uh-hmm.

50:48.523 --> 50:50.525
Well, okay.

50:50.830 --> 50:53.093
♪ Your love is blue

50:53.137 --> 50:54.486
Is this so bad?

50:58.098 --> 50:59.186
Um...

51:00.057 --> 51:01.406
No.

51:02.320 --> 51:04.583
No, this is actually quite nice.

51:04.626 --> 51:07.238
♪ When trouble overtakes you

51:08.630 --> 51:11.372
♪ You better check again

51:12.678 --> 51:15.768
♪ But now my days
Gotten brighter ♪

51:17.552 --> 51:19.250
-♪ And I can see the light...
-Richard?

51:19.859 --> 51:21.600
♪ With you by my side

51:21.643 --> 51:22.862
Richard.

51:26.083 --> 51:28.041
Help. Hey, hey, hey.

51:28.085 --> 51:29.216
Help!

51:40.140 --> 51:41.924
Oh, Jesus Christ, Richard.

51:42.360 --> 51:44.057
What the hell happened?

51:44.101 --> 51:47.016
I'm all right, just calm down.
Don't...

51:47.060 --> 51:48.888
Everything's fine,
I'm all right.

51:48.931 --> 51:50.672
I didn't die. I'm good.

51:52.370 --> 51:53.545
Well, who's that?

51:54.111 --> 51:55.503
That's Santiago.

51:55.547 --> 51:57.114
Who's Santiago?

51:57.505 --> 51:58.898
He's my gardener.

51:58.941 --> 52:00.508
What's your gardener doing here?

52:00.943 --> 52:02.597
He's my emergency contact.

52:03.032 --> 52:04.425
Christ, Richard

52:19.353 --> 52:21.703
Um, can we have a word
in private please?

52:22.008 --> 52:23.966
No, that's fine,
he doesn't speak any English.

52:24.010 --> 52:25.142
Watch this.

52:25.185 --> 52:27.840
Santiago, what day is it?

52:29.276 --> 52:31.800
See? Pancakes

52:34.760 --> 52:36.414
Yes, Lauren Bacall.

52:38.416 --> 52:39.982
Talk. What are you gonna say?
It's fine.

52:41.158 --> 52:43.986
Richard, you've got
to clean up your act.

52:44.335 --> 52:47.642
Yeah. I fucked up.
I'll slow down the candy,

52:47.686 --> 52:50.602
and I'll go green
for a bit, okay?

52:50.906 --> 52:53.257
-Selling grass?
-Marijuana, yeah.

52:53.300 --> 52:54.997
Oh, and where
are you getting it?

52:55.041 --> 52:56.999
Student of mine.
His name is Danny.

52:57.913 --> 53:00.307
Really good kid,
very, very, very smart kid.

53:04.964 --> 53:08.228
Look, I don't want you dying
over something

53:08.272 --> 53:10.796
as infantile as an overdose,
okay?

53:11.927 --> 53:13.059
I'm gonna go out.

53:13.102 --> 53:14.365
Oh.

53:14.408 --> 53:16.932
Oh, or you'll catch something
in the hospital.

53:16.976 --> 53:22.199
Oh, okay. Well, I'll see you
back on, uh, on the campus.

53:22.242 --> 53:23.200
Yeah.

53:23.939 --> 53:25.332
I'll see you back on campus.

53:25.376 --> 53:28.857
Yeah, you said, just go, Pete.
Thanks for coming by.

53:28.901 --> 53:31.033
Yeah, you're looking
good, you're looking good.

53:41.522 --> 53:43.045
Do I look sick to you?

53:44.656 --> 53:46.527
You're in a hospital bed,
Richard.

53:58.887 --> 54:00.846
You wanna say
where you were last night?

54:01.934 --> 54:03.196
Not really.

54:03.849 --> 54:06.721
We had a deal for Olivia.

54:08.723 --> 54:09.811
I know.

54:11.552 --> 54:12.597
I'm sorry.

54:19.908 --> 54:21.083
Are you okay?

54:23.347 --> 54:24.826
Yeah. It's just my back.

54:41.887 --> 54:42.931
Richard?

54:43.932 --> 54:44.933
Yes?

54:46.457 --> 54:48.110
Oh, I'm sorry.
I didn't hear you answer.

54:48.154 --> 54:50.678
Uh, it's Carol,
Henry's secretary.

54:51.505 --> 54:54.987
Uh, Richard, Henry would like
to have a word with you.

54:55.379 --> 54:57.598
-When?
- Now.

54:58.382 --> 54:59.644
Tell him I'm busy.

55:01.167 --> 55:02.429
He says the matter
is rather urgent.

55:02.821 --> 55:04.388
Tell him I'm urgently busy.

55:05.389 --> 55:06.390
Richard.

55:07.913 --> 55:09.044
Yes?

55:11.438 --> 55:13.266
He's ready
to see you now.

55:34.766 --> 55:36.507
Tell me, Richard,
do you like fish?

55:36.550 --> 55:39.248
No. I mean to eat sometimes,

55:39.292 --> 55:41.338
but outside of that, no.
No, I don't.

55:42.339 --> 55:44.602
I believe men could learn
a lot from fish.

55:44.645 --> 55:46.778
That's the most asinine thing
I've ever heard.

55:46.821 --> 55:48.693
Why don't we just cut
to the chase?

55:50.477 --> 55:51.609
All right.

55:52.523 --> 55:55.090
We need to talk
about certain allegations

55:55.134 --> 55:57.136
that have come to my attention,

55:57.179 --> 55:58.877
some of which are serious.

56:00.226 --> 56:01.662
Don't even start.

56:02.184 --> 56:03.229
Excuse me?

56:03.490 --> 56:05.187
I know you heard what I said.

56:05.231 --> 56:06.624
You're simply saying that
for effect.

56:06.667 --> 56:08.887
You want me to repeat myself,
I won't.

56:09.714 --> 56:11.846
I am chancellor
of this university.

56:11.890 --> 56:14.371
I couldn't give
a fucking rat's balls

56:14.849 --> 56:17.852
who the fuck you are.
I have tenure,

56:18.418 --> 56:19.376
and furthermore,

56:21.029 --> 56:22.814
you're in no position of power
when it comes to the two of us.

56:23.815 --> 56:25.556
You're cheating on your wife,
Henry.

56:25.599 --> 56:29.168
You're having an affair,
and not just any affair,

56:29.211 --> 56:32.650
but one with a wife
of a devoted faculty member,

56:33.520 --> 56:34.695
specifically

56:35.740 --> 56:36.828
mine.

56:37.437 --> 56:41.049
Not only that.
But you've allocated funds

56:41.093 --> 56:44.401
from a dwindling budget
for granite erections

56:44.444 --> 56:47.534
that you just littered
throughout this entire campus.

56:48.317 --> 56:51.799
And oddly enough,
they come from the woman

56:51.843 --> 56:53.714
that you're bird dogging
on the side.

56:54.759 --> 56:56.064
Can you remind me

56:56.108 --> 56:58.893
how much does one
of Veronica's works go for?

57:00.721 --> 57:04.856
Chancellor, I have mounted you
like a running stag,

57:04.899 --> 57:07.293
and I am pumping away at you,

57:07.554 --> 57:09.251
like a savage,

57:09.730 --> 57:12.167
and you know it.

57:14.605 --> 57:15.736
Now,

57:17.129 --> 57:18.913
I'm gonna take it
that my request for sabbatical

57:18.957 --> 57:20.698
has been accepted.

57:56.124 --> 57:58.039
Don't look so enthusiastic.

57:58.605 --> 57:59.737
Why would I?

57:59.998 --> 58:02.479
Well, for one,
it's gonna be catered.

