to discover something new

59:19.164 --> 59:20.469
about ourselves.

59:22.384 --> 59:25.910
You, my friend, have been
awarded a sabbatical.

59:26.650 --> 59:27.564
Thank you.

59:29.000 --> 59:30.392
Henry Wright signed
the paperwork, only last week.

59:30.436 --> 59:32.525
- Excuse me.
- See, I told you.

59:32.960 --> 59:34.396
What are you two doing?

59:35.049 --> 59:36.703
Uh we're discussing work.
That's all.

59:36.747 --> 59:39.184
Peter, it's my birthday,

59:40.228 --> 59:42.709
save it for another time,
and come mingle.

59:43.231 --> 59:45.843
-All right.
-And don't close these doors.

59:46.104 --> 59:47.366
No, darling.

59:49.020 --> 59:51.065
Anyway,
Peter was petrified--

59:51.109 --> 59:53.198
Why the hell
did we ever get married?

1:00:04.688 --> 1:00:05.645
You okay?

1:00:07.081 --> 1:00:09.736
Yeah, I'm fine. I'm fine, babe.

1:00:15.263 --> 1:00:16.482
Are you sure?

1:00:17.788 --> 1:00:18.789
Yeah.

1:00:22.706 --> 1:00:24.621
Yeah. I'm gonna be fine.

1:00:26.100 --> 1:00:27.667
The person
one loves at first

1:00:27.711 --> 1:00:29.626
is not the person
one loves at last.

1:00:30.278 --> 1:00:31.628
Love is not an end,

1:00:32.411 --> 1:00:34.500
it's a process through,
which one person attempts

1:00:34.543 --> 1:00:35.632
to know another.

1:00:38.373 --> 1:00:39.374
That's it.

1:00:39.810 --> 1:00:41.899
And in a word?

1:00:42.334 --> 1:00:45.816
In two words,
deceptively simple.

1:00:45.859 --> 1:00:48.427
Beautifully,
beautifully executed.

1:00:48.470 --> 1:00:54.389
And it's a really nice way to
end the class with a little,

1:00:56.130 --> 1:00:57.305
kick in the ass.

1:00:58.045 --> 1:00:59.481
So, you get an A.

1:00:59.830 --> 1:01:01.788
-Thank you.
- You're welcome.

1:01:02.441 --> 1:01:04.573
And I suppose the rest of you
are waiting

1:01:04.835 --> 1:01:09.187
for me to vomit out
some profound words of wisdom.

1:01:09.230 --> 1:01:10.492
Yeah, kind of.

1:01:10.536 --> 1:01:13.060
Oh, thought you'd never ask.

1:01:15.149 --> 1:01:16.847
Come here, give me a hand.

1:01:17.717 --> 1:01:18.718
Thanks.

1:01:18.762 --> 1:01:20.677
-Hey, hey, okay.

1:01:21.678 --> 1:01:22.679
Listen...

1:01:23.462 --> 1:01:26.770
the world needs people
like you.

1:01:28.032 --> 1:01:31.905
The world is literally dying
for your kind.

1:01:33.602 --> 1:01:36.649
Embrace that responsibility,
and you run with it.

1:01:38.129 --> 1:01:40.958
Get out there, earn your keep.
Give back.

1:01:41.828 --> 1:01:44.918
It's not gonna be easy.
Never gonna be easy.

1:01:44.962 --> 1:01:46.528
For much of it,
you'll stand alone

1:01:46.572 --> 1:01:49.357
but you've got to stand strong.

1:01:50.358 --> 1:01:51.751
You know, I beg you

1:01:52.621 --> 1:01:55.363
to not give into mediocrity,

1:01:55.712 --> 1:01:58.062
like the other 98 percent
of the world.

1:01:59.019 --> 1:02:02.022
Because you would be doing
yourselves,

1:02:02.631 --> 1:02:05.634
and the world,
a greatest disservice.

1:02:06.418 --> 1:02:07.941
You're all too smart.

1:02:08.768 --> 1:02:10.814
You're too smart
to let it go to waste.

1:02:11.553 --> 1:02:14.992
And you've got one shot at this.

1:02:15.035 --> 1:02:16.428
One fucking shot.

1:02:18.038 --> 1:02:19.997
Don't let a moment of it
slip by.

1:02:21.433 --> 1:02:23.914
Grab it, snatch it up,
make it yours.

1:02:25.480 --> 1:02:27.004
Celebrate every moment.

1:02:27.831 --> 1:02:29.789
Celebrate every fucking breath.

1:02:33.532 --> 1:02:35.099
I'm telling you, life,

1:02:35.577 --> 1:02:36.927
it's a birdsong.

1:02:46.284 --> 1:02:47.764
Was that it?

1:02:49.374 --> 1:02:52.246
Yeah, I think--I think so, yeah.

1:02:53.291 --> 1:02:54.683
Yeah, that's it.

1:03:22.799 --> 1:03:24.496
Richard? Richard.

1:03:26.280 --> 1:03:27.629
Oh, oh, Richard.

1:03:27.673 --> 1:03:29.806
Oh, no, no, no.
Richard, are you all right?

1:03:30.502 --> 1:03:31.503
Christ.

1:03:32.547 --> 1:03:34.114
-Angels.
-What?

1:03:34.158 --> 1:03:37.422
I hear the angels, Peter,
they're singing.

1:03:37.683 --> 1:03:40.338
No, that's the--that's
the acapella group, Richard.

1:03:41.165 --> 1:03:42.166
Here.

1:03:43.341 --> 1:03:45.604
Why? Why do we have
an acapella group?

1:03:46.126 --> 1:03:48.128
We've always had
an acapella group.

1:03:49.826 --> 1:03:52.741
Well, fuck them.
Can you take me to the bells?

1:03:52.785 --> 1:03:54.874
-What?
-I wanna see the bells.

1:03:55.179 --> 1:03:56.702
-The bells?
-Yeah.

1:03:57.355 --> 1:04:00.358
All right. All right. Come.

1:04:00.401 --> 1:04:02.447
I'll get you
some water first.

1:04:28.865 --> 1:04:29.953
Peter,

1:04:31.389 --> 1:04:35.393
there are a lot of other
good places to sit in here.

1:04:36.133 --> 1:04:37.525
Hmm, yes.

1:04:38.352 --> 1:04:39.484
Of course.

1:04:40.137 --> 1:04:41.138
Yeah.

1:05:02.420 --> 1:05:03.900
Can you feel anything?

1:05:05.902 --> 1:05:06.903
No.

1:05:08.687 --> 1:05:09.993
But I enjoy the lighting.

1:05:11.124 --> 1:05:13.213
-You?
-No.

1:05:14.649 --> 1:05:15.955
But that's all right.

1:05:20.917 --> 1:05:23.267
Please mother of God,
help my friend...

1:05:23.745 --> 1:05:25.312
Afraid it's starting to kick in.

1:05:27.924 --> 1:05:29.012
Does it hurt?

1:05:30.535 --> 1:05:31.753
Oh, fuck yeah.

1:05:32.276 --> 1:05:33.538
Oh, I'm so sorry.

1:05:34.408 --> 1:05:35.583
I'll manage.

1:05:39.283 --> 1:05:41.763
It's fine, Peter.
We knew this was coming.

1:05:43.330 --> 1:05:44.331
Yeah.

1:05:46.725 --> 1:05:48.292
I mean, uh,
I look back on everything,

1:05:48.335 --> 1:05:50.772
and it all somehow
makes so much sense.

1:05:51.077 --> 1:05:54.863
It's as though, uh,
it couldn't be any other way.

1:06:01.348 --> 1:06:03.350
Why's our soul broken?

1:06:04.656 --> 1:06:06.179
Absurd.

1:06:07.615 --> 1:06:08.790
Yet...

1:06:10.053 --> 1:06:11.315
It's perfect.

1:06:13.665 --> 1:06:16.494
And it's also perfect
when you look at it.

1:06:16.537 --> 1:06:18.409
-You know what I mean?
-Yeah.

1:06:32.771 --> 1:06:34.686
It's gonna be hard
to leave this place.

1:06:39.430 --> 1:06:41.475
It's gonna be hard
to say goodbye.

1:06:42.955 --> 1:06:45.697
Richard, I'm gonna miss you.

1:06:47.438 --> 1:06:50.049
I'm gonna miss you too, Peter.
If I'm able.

1:06:52.660 --> 1:06:54.880
Fuck, I'm going to cry.

1:06:54.923 --> 1:06:56.360
-No.
-Dear God.

1:06:56.621 --> 1:06:58.188
-Please.

1:06:58.231 --> 1:06:59.841
Please don't do this.
No, no, shh.

1:06:59.885 --> 1:07:01.930
-Dammit.
-No, no, no. Listen.

1:07:02.322 --> 1:07:04.194
I really prefer
if you didn't cry.

1:07:04.237 --> 1:07:06.892
-Listen to me. We tried.

1:07:06.935 --> 1:07:10.287
-Yes. Yes.
-Now let's go. Come on.

1:07:10.765 --> 1:07:12.419
-Come on.

1:07:12.463 --> 1:07:13.464
Okay.

1:07:14.247 --> 1:07:15.814
-I'm sorry.
-Come on.

1:07:15.857 --> 1:07:17.120
It's all right.

1:07:18.512 --> 1:07:19.644
Come on, Peter.

1:07:22.255 --> 1:07:23.300
-Oh.

1:07:30.263 --> 1:07:32.048
You're a good man, Richard.

1:07:32.874 --> 1:07:34.354
So are you, my friend.

1:07:35.877 --> 1:07:37.662
Thank you for being
so good to me.

1:07:37.705 --> 1:07:41.057
I'm trying, Richard.
I'm trying.

1:07:43.798 --> 1:07:46.192
Isn't it strange
how natural this feels?

1:07:46.236 --> 1:07:48.151
- Yeah.
- Two men,

1:07:48.194 --> 1:07:51.023
holding one another,
passionately, in a church.

1:07:51.632 --> 1:07:54.070
Groping one another freely.

1:07:57.203 --> 1:07:58.248
Yeah.

1:07:59.684 --> 1:08:00.467
-Oh, you're stupid.
- Come on you, pervert.

1:08:23.925 --> 1:08:24.926
Hey.

1:08:26.624 --> 1:08:27.625
Bye.

1:08:30.236 --> 1:08:31.672
You're going out tonight?

1:08:31.716 --> 1:08:32.717
Yeah.

1:08:33.761 --> 1:08:34.762
Okay.

1:08:35.763 --> 1:08:37.243
You have fun, okay?

1:08:38.940 --> 1:08:40.333
Yeah, you, too.

1:08:41.943 --> 1:08:45.512
I'm not sure that's possible,
but I'm promising you

1:08:45.556 --> 1:08:47.123
that we will try.

1:08:50.517 --> 1:08:51.823
Go get 'em, kid.

1:08:57.220 --> 1:08:58.177
Bye, dad.

1:09:12.452 --> 1:09:15.586
Thank you so much
for coming, really.

1:09:15.629 --> 1:09:18.502
Oh, oh, you get just lovelier
every year.

1:09:19.416 --> 1:09:22.288
Veronica, Richard.
Our guest of honor.

1:09:22.897 --> 1:09:24.116
So nice you could make it.

1:09:24.160 --> 1:09:25.770
Oh, we wouldn't miss it
for the world.

1:09:25.813 --> 1:09:27.119
How do you do?
Hi, I'm Richard.

1:09:28.207 --> 1:09:30.078
Oh, okay.

1:09:30.122 --> 1:09:31.819
That's a hell of a greeting.

1:09:34.474 --> 1:09:36.650
I'm going to the bar.

1:09:39.827 --> 1:09:40.828
Hi.

1:09:41.307 --> 1:09:42.308
Hi.

1:09:43.614 --> 1:09:44.876
Peter and I have decided
to stay in this year,

1:09:44.919 --> 1:09:46.965
and spend Christmas in Miami.

1:09:47.008 --> 1:09:49.707
- Hello.
-Oh, how fashionable.

1:09:49.750 --> 1:09:52.536
Donna, you weren't
at my birthday party. Why?

1:09:54.886 --> 1:09:57.105
I've been so wanting to tell you

1:09:57.149 --> 1:09:59.282
-that I mixed up the date.
-Oh.

1:09:59.325 --> 1:10:01.632
Excuse me everyone,
if I could have your attention.

1:10:01.675 --> 1:10:04.722
Dinner is to be served shortly,
so, if you would be so kind

1:10:04.765 --> 1:10:06.680
as to begin migrating
to the dining room,

1:10:06.724 --> 1:10:08.378
that would be much appreciated.

1:10:13.034 --> 1:10:15.472
Veronica.
You'll be right here next to me.

1:10:15.515 --> 1:10:17.125
-Richard.

1:10:17.169 --> 1:10:18.997
Uh, no, no, no.
Tight Quarters, I'm afraid.

1:10:19.040 --> 1:10:20.346
He'll be somewhere in the back.

1:10:26.570 --> 1:10:27.919
Hello, everyone.

1:10:28.572 --> 1:10:32.489
Um, sorry, why isn't Richard
sitting at this table?

1:10:32.532 --> 1:10:34.099
I can assure you
that there has been

1:10:34.142 --> 1:10:35.448
a great deal of thought

1:10:35.492 --> 1:10:37.537
that's going
into the seating arrangements.

1:10:43.021 --> 1:10:44.022
What?

1:10:44.283 --> 1:10:45.676
Dead, gone.

1:10:45.719 --> 1:10:48.505
Oh, that's horrible.
What was it?

1:10:48.853 --> 1:10:51.159
Oh, melanoma, I'm afraid.

1:10:51.203 --> 1:10:54.554
Oh. Oh, welcome,
young man.

1:10:55.947 --> 1:10:57.340
And the families?

1:10:57.383 --> 1:10:58.645
Honestly,

1:10:58.906 --> 1:11:00.952
-you don't wanna know.
-Oh, really?

1:11:04.564 --> 1:11:06.349
While everyone's being served,

1:11:06.392 --> 1:11:08.568
I just wanted to say
a couple words.

1:11:08.873 --> 1:11:13.051
On behalf of both myself
and my lovely wife, welcome.

1:11:13.094 --> 1:11:14.487
It's an honor to have each

1:11:14.531 --> 1:11:16.446
and every one of you
here tonight.

1:11:16.489 --> 1:11:20.101
Now, I know I'm not alone
when I say that this quarter

1:11:20.363 --> 1:11:22.452
may have been our very best.

1:11:22.930 --> 1:11:25.193
And the opportunity to serve,

1:11:25.237 --> 1:11:27.413
as your president
and chancellor,

1:11:27.674 --> 1:11:31.287
has been nothing short
of humbling.

1:11:33.201 --> 1:11:34.551
So thank you.

1:11:34.594 --> 1:11:36.292
I can only hope

1:11:36.596 --> 1:11:39.512
to live up to the high standards
that you have set.

1:11:39.556 --> 1:11:41.253
- We will.
- Cheers.

1:11:41.297 --> 1:11:45.083
Now, let us eat
for the night is young.

1:11:47.999 --> 1:11:50.915
Oh, that was a lovely speech.

1:11:50.958 --> 1:11:52.046
Beautiful.

1:11:52.090 --> 1:11:53.526
Did you actually
buy that shit, really?

1:11:54.397 --> 1:11:55.398
Excuse me?

1:11:56.616 --> 1:11:58.923
Are you in the
communications department?

1:12:27.995 --> 1:12:30.258
I have something
that I would like to say.

1:12:32.522 --> 1:12:34.045
Could you stop playing that

1:12:34.088 --> 1:12:36.308
before I heave this knife
in your direction?

1:12:36.352 --> 1:12:37.831
- Thank you.

1:12:37.875 --> 1:12:39.616
Uh, young lady with the wine,
would you mind

1:12:39.659 --> 1:12:42.532
just standing right by my side,
and never leave?

1:12:43.010 --> 1:12:44.838
Because I have much to say

1:12:45.752 --> 1:12:47.972
-and many to toast.
-Oh, my God.

1:12:48.015 --> 1:12:51.192
Those of you who do not know,
my name is Richard Brown.

1:12:52.193 --> 1:12:53.412
Professor of English.

1:12:53.847 --> 1:12:56.328
Oh, uh, cheers to me.

1:12:57.111 --> 1:12:58.374
Cheers.

1:12:58.417 --> 1:13:00.027
-Cheers.
- To Richard.

1:13:01.028 --> 1:13:05.381
Henry Wright, on behalf
of every one of us here,

1:13:05.424 --> 1:13:08.732
let me, please, express
our gratitude,

1:13:09.863 --> 1:13:12.910
-for this finely forced evening.
-I'm sorry.

1:13:12.953 --> 1:13:14.868
The commitment
that you have shown

1:13:14.912 --> 1:13:19.438
to the students, faculty,
even the wives of the faculty...

1:13:21.353 --> 1:13:22.963
...is very, very impressive.

1:13:23.355 --> 1:13:24.791
You've outdone yourself.

1:13:26.358 --> 1:13:27.403
And it shows.

1:13:28.491 --> 1:13:32.146
As far as I'm concerned,
three balls...

1:13:32.973 --> 1:13:34.975
-deserves three cheers.
- No.

1:13:35.759 --> 1:13:37.543
All right, Richard,
I think that's enough.

1:13:37.587 --> 1:13:40.981
Henry, do not
interrupt me while I'm talking.

1:13:41.025 --> 1:13:43.027
Particularly in front
of so many people.

1:13:43.070 --> 1:13:45.029
-Do you understand?
-No, I don't understand.

1:13:45.072 --> 1:13:46.160
Yeah.

1:13:46.204 --> 1:13:47.510
Nobody has
three testicles.

1:13:47.553 --> 1:13:48.772
To Peter Matthew.

1:13:48.815 --> 1:13:50.077
-Oh.
- Oh.

1:13:50.121 --> 1:13:51.209
Gotta shut up.

1:13:52.384 --> 1:13:54.342
Your heart is truly
one of gold.

1:13:54.386 --> 1:13:56.867
- It is.
-And this college is...

1:13:57.171 --> 1:13:59.217
-very lucky to have you.
- Hmm, that's true.

1:13:59.260 --> 1:14:01.524
Of course, thank you
for your hard work.

1:14:01.567 --> 1:14:04.483
But most important, thank you

1:14:05.310 --> 1:14:06.572
for being a true friend.

1:14:06.616 --> 1:14:08.487
- Oh, to Peter, cheers.
- Cheers.

1:14:08.531 --> 1:14:09.749
To Peter.

1:14:09.793 --> 1:14:12.491
Also there are some
parting words

1:14:12.535 --> 1:14:14.885
that I feel like I owe.

1:14:15.625 --> 1:14:17.714
Because this will be
the last time

1:14:17.757 --> 1:14:19.846
that I ever see any of you.

1:14:21.413 --> 1:14:26.244
For not only have I been awarded
a sabbatical, um...

1:14:26.897 --> 1:14:28.725
This is strange,
Peter.

1:14:31.641 --> 1:14:33.338
...I'm gonna die.

1:14:34.731 --> 1:14:36.515
Yeah...

1:14:37.081 --> 1:14:39.126
-I'm gonna die,

1:14:39.170 --> 1:14:43.217
and I'm gonna die much sooner
than I had imagined.

1:14:45.568 --> 1:14:47.004
Oh, my goodness.

1:14:49.093 --> 1:14:50.355
I know, dear.

1:14:50.398 --> 1:14:53.053
-What is he talking about?
-Shh.

1:14:53.097 --> 1:14:55.621
So in preparing
for what lies ahead,

1:14:56.274 --> 1:14:59.495
I've come to realize
that for much of my life,

1:15:00.974 --> 1:15:02.454
I've been mistaken,

1:15:03.977 --> 1:15:05.936
and I failed.

1:15:05.979 --> 1:15:10.941
I failed, not only
to comprehend my mortality,

1:15:11.942 --> 1:15:13.596
but I've failed
to appreciate it.

1:15:14.640 --> 1:15:16.120
And as a result,

1:15:18.339 --> 1:15:21.604
